article_text:
JinkoSolar Holding Co. on Thursday reported a better-than-expected 36.5% jump in revenue in its first quarter as the cell-and-module maker benefits from expansion and higher shipments.

Shares, up 44% this year, added 4.9% in premarket trading.

article_summary:
Shares, up 44% this year, added 4.9% in premarket trading.
JinkoSolar Holding Co. on Thursday reported a better-than-expected 36.5% jump in revenue in its first quarter as the cell-and-module maker benefits from expansion and higher shipments.
